ABOUT THE 2021 GOLDEN GLOBE AWARDS:
The 78th Golden Globes will take place on February 28, coast to coast from 4 pm to 8 pm PT/7-11 ET on NBC. The event will be hosted by Tina Fey and Amy Poehler, returning for the fourth time, after hosting in 2013, 2014, and 2015. Fey and Poehler will share duties from their respective cities, with Fey on the East Coast and Poehler on the West Coast. Fey will be live from New Yorkâ€™s Rainbow Room, Poehler will be live from the Beverly Hilton, in Beverly Hills, and nominees, from various locations around the world.
